        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Twilio SMS channel",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add bundled `sms` channel support with Twilio inbound webhooks, signed request validation, pairing/allowlist access, and outbound text replies.\n- Wire account resolution, env-only defaults, named `defaultAccount`, route-session keys, replay dedupe, chunked outbound delivery, config metadata, docs, labels, and plugin inventory reference docs.\n- Add Twilio Messaging Service SID sender support, SMS plain-text markdown flattening, guarded Twilio API fetches, and AccountSid/SmsMessageSid webhook validation.\n- Preserve shared pairing account context so approval notifications can use the correct channel account.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --write extensions/sms docs/channels/sms.md`\n- `pnpm exec tsgo -p extensions/sms/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-vitest-sms-compare node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/sms/src/phone.test.ts extensions/sms/src/accounts.test.ts extensions/sms/src/twilio.test.ts extensions/sms/src/inbound.test.ts extensions/sms/src/gateway.test.ts extensions/sms/src/channel.test.ts extensions/sms/src/send.test.ts extensions/sms/src/webhook.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm plugins:inventory:check`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Local structured review: clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: OpenClaw now exposes a standalone Twilio-backed SMS channel with signed inbound webhooks, pairing/allowlist access, Messaging Service or phone-number outbound replies, chunking, config metadata, labels, and docs.\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout on macOS, Node/pnpm repo toolchain.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Commands listed in Verification above, plus GitHub label creation for `channel: sms`.\nEvidence after fix: Focused SMS Vitest shard passed 8 files / 26 tests; generated plugin inventory and bundled channel config metadata checks passed; SMS extension typecheck passed; local structured review reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: Unknown SMS senders in pairing mode receive a pairing challenge, allowed senders route through the canonical session key, duplicate webhook paths and replayed message SIDs are rejected, signed form values are preserved for Twilio verification, mismatched Twilio AccountSid is rejected, env-only configuration starts the default account, long replies are chunked after plain-text cleanup, and `fromNumber` takes precedence when both Twilio sender styles are resolved.\nWhat was not tested: Live Twilio webhook delivery against a real Twilio phone number. A full `pnpm build` rerun reached compile/UI phases after the final sender-precedence fix, but the unrelated CLI startup metadata helper timed out rendering browser help under local machine load.\n",
